National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Israeli National Security Advisor Meir Ben-Shabbat to express the United States' concerns about the situation in Jerusalem. They discussed the violent confrontations at the Haram al-Sharif / Temple Mount during Ramadan and recent engagements by senior U.S. officials with Israeli and Palestinian officials to deescalate tensions and denounce violence. Sullivan also reiterated concerns about the potential evictions of Palestinian families in Sheikh Jarrah. They agreed that rocket attacks and incendiary balloons from Gaza towards Israel are unacceptable. Sullivan encouraged the Israeli government to take appropriate measures to ensure calm during Jerusalem Day commemorations. He also assured Ben-Shabbat of the U.S.' commitment to Israel's security and promoting peace and stability in the Middle East.